	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>NES games with sprites smaller than 16 x 16 pixels</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was wondering: Are there any NES games where the main sprites (i.e. not things like bullets or the character's representation on a map view) are smaller than 16 x 16 pixels?<br />I guess &quot;Lemmings&quot; had very small sprites, but that's basically because the game is supposed to have a whole lot of characters on the screen.<br />Are there games where the characters are just 8 x 16 or even 8 x 8 pixels big, but where the number of the characters on screen isn't any bigger than in games like &quot;Mario&quot; or &quot;Zelda&quot;?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
